set_socv_repor...gma_multiplier(25.10)  set_socv_repor...gma_multiplier(25.10)

Name
       set_socv_reporting_nsigma_multiplier  -  Controls n-sigma value for re-
       porting purposes

Syntax
       set_socv_reporting_nsigma_multiplier

       [-help]

       [-view <list_of_views>]

       {[-setup <float>] [-hold <float>]}

       [-transition <float>]

       Controls n-sigma value for reporting purposes.

       This command supports n-sigma specification  per  view  per  setup/hold
       combination.

Parameters
       -help  Prints out the command usage.

       -hold <float>
              Specifies the sigma multiplier for hold mode.

       -setup <float>
              Specifies the sigma multiplier for setup mode.

       -transition <float>
              Specifies the sigma multiplier to use for transition related DRV
              checks     -     including    max_transition,    min_transition,
              pulse_clock_max_transition, and pulse_clock_min_transition.

              When this parameter is not specified, the sigma multiplier spec-
              ified for setup will be used for transitions.

              When the -transition parameter is specified,  you  can  set  the
              timing_report_max_transition_check_using_nsigma_slew      global
              variable to true to report transition related DRV  checks,  such
              as,  max_transition, min_transition, pulse_clock_max_transition,
              and pulse_clock_min_transition. This  setting  enables  the  re-
              port_constraint  command  to  use mean and sigma slew values for
              reporting transition values in DRV checks.

       -view <list_of_views>
              Applies the sigma multiplier factor to  the  specified  list  of
              analysis views.

              Note: The specified views should be active.

Examples
              * The  following  command  applies  the  sigma multiplier to the
                specified view in setup mode :

                set_socv_reporting_nsigma_multiplier    -setup    2.5    -view
                std_max_setup

              * The  following  command  applies  the  sigma multiplier to the
                specified view in for hold mode:

                set_socv_reporting_nsigma_multiplier    -hold    3.0     -view
                std_min_hold

